7/7 by embracing lower financial returns, philanthropic #impinv can support #socent that are seeking to serve the most marginal populations.
6/7 #impinv typically assume that it’s up to social entrepreneurs to figure out how to increase earned income to boost ROI.
5/7 generating market-rate returns for #impinv isn’t the right path for all #socent that provide useful products/services to the poor.
4/7 need & opp for some #impinv to accept below-market-rate returns, but #impinv studies on financial perf. argue the opposite
3/7 capital-starved social biz w growth prospects but little chance of producing market-rate returns soon = ideal 4 philanthropic #impinv.
2/7 enterprises with unproven models, or that focus on serving the poorest of the poor, find most #impinv $$ out of reach.
